- Prior full rabies vaccination means no need for rabies immune globulin (RIG);  
- Post-exposure treatment requires only two doses of rabies vaccine—at Days 0 and 3—as per global standards including those from WHO and CDC—even for mild wounds such as a cut on the big toe;

Final decision matches initial suggestion but grounded more precisely by evidence-based protocols regarding dose timing and necessity of RIG.

